  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When executing an external script the Truffle console prints this message:\r\n\r\n`Note that all scripts *must* call process.exit() when finished.`\r\n\r\nThis is in contradiction to what the document page says for writing external scripts:\r\n\r\nhttp://truffleframework.com/docs/getting_started/scripts\r\n\r\n_\"You can do anything you'd like within this script, so long as the callback is called when the script finishes. The callback accepts an error as its first and only parameter. If an error is provided, execution will halt and the process will return a non-zero exit code.\"_\r\n\r\nI followed the information given in the docs and my script worked fine.",
